[Two-coin probability space with finite set-valued probability measure]
 Under the new set-valued requirement, the probability measure in the first
 example becomes: 
\begin_inset Formula 
\[
\begin{array}{c@{\qquad\qquad}c}
\begin{array}{rcl}
\pmeas(\emptyset) & = & \imposs\\
\pmeas(\{HH\}) & = & \poss\\
\pmeas(\{HT\}) & = & \imposs\\
\pmeas(\{TH\}) & = & \poss\\
\pmeas(\{TT\}) & = & \imposs\\
\pmeas(\{HH,HT\}) & = & \poss\\
\pmeas(\{HH,TH\}) & = & \poss\\
\pmeas(\{HH,TT\}) & = & \poss
\end{array} & \begin{array}{rcl}
\pmeas(\{HT,TH\}) & = & \poss\\
\pmeas(\{HT,TT\}) & = & \imposs\\
\pmeas(\{TH,TT\}) & = & \poss\\
\pmeas(\{HH,HT,TH\}) & = & \poss\\
\pmeas(\{HH,HT,TT\}) & = & \poss\\
\pmeas(\{HH,TH,TT\}) & = & \poss\\
\pmeas(\{HT,TH,TT\}) & = & \poss\\
\pmeas(\{HH,HT,TH,TT\}) & = & \poss
\end{array}\end{array}
\]

\end_inset

